# Workflow Candidate Ledger

Track workflow ideas and portfolio-shaping options.

This ledger should not become a to-do list for endless workflow sprawl. It should help decide whether to reuse, adapt, compose, refine, decompose, merge, retire, or create workflow packages.

For each candidate, capture:

- candidate name
- candidate type:
  - existing workflow to reuse
  - existing workflow to adapt
  - existing workflows to compose
  - existing workflow to refine
  - existing workflow to decompose
  - workflow to merge or retire
  - new workflow package
  - reusable building block
- starting situation
- terminal outcome
- sponsor/user
- why it matters
- existing workflows/building blocks checked first
- reuse/adaptation/composition/decomposition assessment
- missing capability exposed
- whether it was chosen, deferred, rejected, merged, retired, or superseded
- cycle references

## New Workflow Gate

Do not create a new workflow package unless all are true:

- At least three existing workflows/building blocks were checked for reuse or adaptation.
- The candidate cannot be expressed as a parameterized run, composition, adaptation, refinement, or decomposition of existing workflows.
- The candidate has a distinct terminal artifact package and sponsor/use case.
- The implementation reuses existing stdlib/helper seams where applicable.
- The new workflow does not introduce a new validation idiom that should instead be shared.
- The new workflow reduces future ambiguity more than it increases portfolio size.

